description:
Advanced SingleTon 

if you want any class to be Singleton, instead of MonoBehaviour use SingleTon<ClassName>
Example
class MyClass : SingleTon<MyClass>
{
public void ExampleMethod(){ }

}

--> To access, use MyClass.GetInstance.ExampleMethod();

--> If you find issues relating singletone, USE    this.InitialiseInstance()  in Awake

-->If the class is attached to Gameobject, make sure to name gameobject same as class name that is being used as singleton
